1
00:00:12,930 --> 00:00:15,099
For the curtain,

2
00:00:15,182 --> 00:00:18,269
you will choose between these.

3
00:00:18,352 --> 00:00:20,020
-Correct.
-Understood.

4
00:00:21,397 --> 00:00:26,277
We'll bring the revised layout next time.

5
00:00:26,360 --> 00:00:27,653
Thank you.

6
00:00:31,365 --> 00:00:33,117
I'm a little hungry.

7
00:00:34,326 --> 00:00:37,163
There's a dish
I can whip up really quickly.

8
00:00:38,289 --> 00:00:40,791
You're invited to have some too
if you're free, Diane.

9
00:00:41,709 --> 00:00:43,252
-Are you sure?
-Of course.

10
00:00:43,335 --> 00:00:45,588
-Thank you.
-Don't mention it.

11
00:00:52,303 --> 00:00:53,304
Here you go.

12
00:00:54,180 --> 00:00:55,598
Is that an omelet?

13
00:00:55,681 --> 00:00:59,185
It's my family's recipe.
We call it "om-ham egg."

14
00:00:59,268 --> 00:01:00,478
Om-ham egg?

15
00:01:00,561 --> 00:01:04,231
That's right. Thinly sliced pieces
of ham wrapped with egg.

16
00:01:04,315 --> 00:01:07,735
It's my mother's recipe,
and I gave it a name.

17
00:01:08,402 --> 00:01:10,237
Oh, yes. The other day,

18
00:01:10,321 --> 00:01:14,033
I watched a program on TV where they paid
a visit to Shingetsu Nathan's mansion.

19
00:01:14,116 --> 00:01:16,368
The fortune teller with the catchphrase
"Soar, dragon!" right?

20
00:01:16,452 --> 00:01:17,661
Haven't heard that in a while.

21
00:01:17,745 --> 00:01:21,832
So he lives in a massive estate.
He practically owns an entire mountain.

22
00:01:21,916 --> 00:01:25,878
But what surprised me was his food.

23
00:01:25,961 --> 00:01:28,214
His bar snack
looked just like my om-ham egg.

24
00:01:28,297 --> 00:01:29,465
-Really.
-Wow.

25
00:01:29,965 --> 00:01:34,303
For someone so wealthy, he's got
such a cheap preference for his snack.

26
00:01:37,097 --> 00:01:39,558
This was my family's side dish.

27
00:01:40,893 --> 00:01:44,271
Sorry. I'd give this a 10 out of 10
as a side dish.

28
00:01:46,148 --> 00:01:47,149
Thanks for the food.

29
00:01:48,150 --> 00:01:50,194
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

30
00:01:57,618 --> 00:01:58,702
Yum.

31
00:01:58,786 --> 00:02:00,830
How's the flavor? Not too cheap?

32
00:02:00,913 --> 00:02:02,206
Come on.

33
00:02:02,957 --> 00:02:06,252
Taste of home is different for everyone.

34
00:02:06,335 --> 00:02:09,839
By the way, ours was
ramen with uncooked mozuku seaweed.

35
00:02:09,922 --> 00:02:11,549
Uncooked mozuku seaweed.

36
00:02:11,632 --> 00:02:13,175
The unseasoned kind.

37
00:02:13,801 --> 00:02:17,096
Guess mozuku seaweed
is just as bland as someone I know.

38
00:02:18,389 --> 00:02:19,598
What was that?

39
00:02:20,975 --> 00:02:22,726
This isn't my parents' recipe,

40
00:02:22,810 --> 00:02:25,104
but we cook tomato in our oden soup.

41
00:02:26,188 --> 00:02:29,525
Your ex-husband
is a professional chef, after all.

42
00:02:30,234 --> 00:02:33,612
There you go again,
blabbering on about her personal life.

43
00:02:35,573 --> 00:02:39,076
I thought it'd be fine
since they're already split… Sorry.

44
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:43,873
Thanks to you, I know a lot
about everyone's personal lives.

45
00:02:47,418 --> 00:02:49,128
Taste of home. Huh.

46
00:02:50,254 --> 00:02:52,965
My family didn't have one.
Our food tasted like the maid's cooking

47
00:02:53,048 --> 00:02:55,384
and the recipes my mother learned
from her cooking studio.

48
00:02:57,219 --> 00:02:59,638
In a sense, you grew up
with restaurant-level home cooking.

49
00:03:01,891 --> 00:03:03,142
So this is what they call

50
00:03:03,726 --> 00:03:06,103
"the taste of home."

51
00:03:20,326 --> 00:03:24,121
Hello. Everyone.
I'm Ichikawa of Icchi Channel.

52
00:03:24,204 --> 00:03:26,040
Icchi breezy!

53
00:03:26,123 --> 00:03:28,417
Today's content is…

54
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:32,087
"I confronted a sketchy business!
Episode three."

55
00:03:32,171 --> 00:03:34,381
That's right, episode three!

56
00:03:34,465 --> 00:03:37,343
This is Fortune-Telling House, Sort.

57
00:03:37,426 --> 00:03:40,721
Here we are, folks. What do you think?

58
00:03:40,804 --> 00:03:43,557
Look at this shady mansion.
How do I put it…

59
00:03:44,266 --> 00:03:47,186
Are you the rumored fortune teller?

60
00:03:47,269 --> 00:03:49,813
-Hey, what's up?
-Can you stop recording?

61
00:03:50,564 --> 00:03:53,651
Oh, what? But I don't see any signs.

62
00:03:54,818 --> 00:03:57,571
Nothing says "No recording."

63
00:03:57,655 --> 00:03:59,657
-Yes, but…
-Is there?

64
00:04:00,491 --> 00:04:03,202
-It's fine, yeah?
-No, it's not fine.

65
00:04:03,285 --> 00:04:05,746
Shall we go inside? Let's go, guys!

66
00:04:05,829 --> 00:04:08,123
-Let's go, let's go!
-Seriously, please stop!

67
00:04:08,207 --> 00:04:10,876
What is this place?

68
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:13,045
-Is this the reception desk?
-Okay, seriously…

69
00:04:13,128 --> 00:04:16,340
Look at these mystical books
about divination.

70
00:04:16,423 --> 00:04:20,386
While we don't have a sign up,
for privacy reasons, you can't…

71
00:04:20,469 --> 00:04:23,055
-Wait, wait. But wait.
-I'm serious. Stop.

72
00:04:23,138 --> 00:04:25,683
-There's no client, so it's okay, right?
-Come on.

73
00:04:25,766 --> 00:04:27,101
It's not okay.

74
00:04:27,184 --> 00:04:29,269
Don't worry about my privacy.

75
00:04:29,353 --> 00:04:31,563
-Seriously, don't.
-Hey, hey…

76
00:04:31,647 --> 00:04:34,108
-Watch out, watch out.
-You can't be in here. Please!

77
00:04:34,191 --> 00:04:36,610
-Look at these never-before-seen…
-Stop it!

78
00:04:36,694 --> 00:04:39,780
-…curiosities lying about.
-Let's settle down.

79
00:04:42,032 --> 00:04:45,035
I reported you to the police
for obstruction of business.

80
00:04:45,703 --> 00:04:48,580
Please standby until the police arrive.

81
00:04:48,664 --> 00:04:49,832
The police?

82
00:04:51,750 --> 00:04:53,043
This is big.

83
00:04:53,127 --> 00:04:56,130
We're gonna go viral! Hell yeah!

84
00:04:56,213 --> 00:04:57,840
The police are comin'!

85
00:04:57,923 --> 00:05:00,592
-Hold on, hold on.
-Wait, wait!

86
00:05:00,676 --> 00:05:02,761
-Seriously!
-A mysterious lady came.

87
00:05:02,845 --> 00:05:04,638
-Stop it!
-Okay, okay!

88
00:05:17,484 --> 00:05:18,861
-Chloe.
-Emma.

89
00:05:18,944 --> 00:05:20,154
-Chloe et Emma.
-Chloe et Emma.

90
00:05:28,704 --> 00:05:30,164
I'm done drying your hair.

91
00:05:30,247 --> 00:05:31,373
Thank you.

92
00:05:31,915 --> 00:05:34,168
What an exhausting day.

93
00:05:34,251 --> 00:05:36,336
I can't believe
we had to get the police involved.

94
00:05:37,087 --> 00:05:38,213
Hey.

95
00:05:38,297 --> 00:05:42,009
I've thought this for a while, but
haven't things been kind of off lately?

96
00:05:42,092 --> 00:05:43,093
What?

97
00:05:43,177 --> 00:05:45,054
We've been getting more male clients,

98
00:05:45,137 --> 00:05:48,849
and it's like they don't take
fortune telling all that seriously.

99
00:05:50,642 --> 00:05:54,772
We don't have a website
or a social media account.

100
00:05:54,855 --> 00:05:56,899
How do they hear about us?

101
00:05:58,484 --> 00:05:59,860
I knew it.

102
00:06:01,236 --> 00:06:02,362
Look at this.

103
00:06:03,655 --> 00:06:07,409
Someone listed my business on Maps.

104
00:06:07,493 --> 00:06:09,369
On top of that, they left a review.

105
00:06:09,453 --> 00:06:10,788
You're right.

106
00:06:11,371 --> 00:06:12,623
"Molly."

107
00:06:13,248 --> 00:06:16,126
"At this shop, a beautiful,
android-like girl wearing a gaudy dress

108
00:06:16,210 --> 00:06:18,087
throws cards in the air.
It's a total sham.

109
00:06:18,170 --> 00:06:19,213
SORT - MOLLY

110
00:06:19,296 --> 00:06:21,090
The fortune telling is nothing special.

111
00:06:21,173 --> 00:06:23,801
Actually, what the hell
are Chronicle cards?

112
00:06:23,884 --> 00:06:25,010
Lol."

113
00:06:25,886 --> 00:06:30,015
That pisses me off to no end,
but nothing they said is wrong.

114
00:06:30,099 --> 00:06:33,227
The info about my appearance
breaches my privacy,

115
00:06:33,310 --> 00:06:35,771
and calling my fortune telling
a sham is libel.

116
00:06:35,854 --> 00:06:38,524
This has affected our client base.
It's been a real problem.

117
00:06:39,108 --> 00:06:40,859
We even had to call the police.

118
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:42,903
Can't you get this review taken down?

119
00:06:43,403 --> 00:06:45,030
Let's see…

120
00:06:46,448 --> 00:06:48,033
"Create a business account,

121
00:06:48,117 --> 00:06:51,245
and register as a business owner
to request the removal of a comment."

122
00:06:51,328 --> 00:06:52,329
But…

123
00:06:52,412 --> 00:06:53,705
FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS

124
00:06:54,665 --> 00:06:57,376
Apparently, as long as the post
reflects the poster's actual experience,

125
00:06:57,459 --> 00:07:00,504
it won't be taken down, even if it's
negative or intended to harm the business.

126
00:07:00,587 --> 00:07:01,922
Say what?

127
00:07:02,548 --> 00:07:07,427
"An honest review of a bad experience
won't be removed."

128
00:07:09,471 --> 00:07:13,892
Also, this poster's profile
is set to private.

129
00:07:13,976 --> 00:07:15,978
They're playing it safe.
This won't be easy.

130
00:07:21,483 --> 00:07:22,693
What's the matter?

131
00:07:23,193 --> 00:07:25,195
Opening up the client registry.

132
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:30,159
Based on the posted date…

133
00:07:32,828 --> 00:07:34,121
Found him.

134
00:07:34,204 --> 00:07:36,623
Must be this guy, Yukio Obayashi.

135
00:07:36,707 --> 00:07:37,875
YUKIO OBAYASHI

136
00:07:37,958 --> 00:07:41,170
But trolls like this
may have used an alias.

137
00:07:42,171 --> 00:07:44,590
The account name on Maps is Molly.

138
00:07:45,174 --> 00:07:47,926
His real name
must include "Mori," or "forest."

139
00:07:48,010 --> 00:07:51,346
That's why his alias contains "bayashi,"
meaning "the woods."

140
00:07:52,848 --> 00:07:54,266
Molly, you!

141
00:07:55,809 --> 00:07:58,604
"An honest review of a bad experience…"

142
00:07:59,271 --> 00:08:00,397
I see.

143
00:08:01,481 --> 00:08:02,649
In that case,

144
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:06,612
an eye for an eye,
a bad experience for a bad experience.

145
00:08:09,907 --> 00:08:11,992
REPLY

146
00:08:12,075 --> 00:08:14,578
DEAR MOLLY

147
00:08:31,094 --> 00:08:33,597
You wrote this, Chloe?

148
00:08:35,015 --> 00:08:36,808
Did anything sound off?

149
00:08:36,892 --> 00:08:41,313
The phrasing may be polite,
but what you pointed out is harsh.

150
00:08:41,813 --> 00:08:44,650
The last few sentences especially sting.

151
00:08:45,525 --> 00:08:46,818
"A sincere question

152
00:08:46,902 --> 00:08:49,696
gets a sincere answer in fortune telling.

153
00:08:49,780 --> 00:08:53,492
But a sloppy question will be met
with an answer that's just as sloppy.

154
00:08:53,575 --> 00:08:55,285
Only people with sincere hearts

155
00:08:55,369 --> 00:08:58,705
ask sincere questions.

156
00:09:00,415 --> 00:09:04,044
Should you ever sincerely
seek guidance from fortune telling,

157
00:09:04,127 --> 00:09:06,505
I will be glad to help you then."

158
00:09:07,965 --> 00:09:11,635
Don't pick a fight with a business
that has no interest in turning a profit.

159
00:09:11,718 --> 00:09:14,596
Is this okay?
What if you poured gasoline on fire?

160
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:16,932
With all this taunting,
he just might show his face again.

161
00:09:17,015 --> 00:09:18,433
What?

162
00:09:18,517 --> 00:09:21,228
I think I'll have the security company
that handles the main house

163
00:09:21,311 --> 00:09:24,273
install security cameras
in the reception area.

164
00:09:24,356 --> 00:09:26,775
We'll sort it out one way or another.
Good night.

165
00:09:30,904 --> 00:09:32,322
I'm getting scared.

166
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:45,043
Security camera. Huh.

167
00:09:47,170 --> 00:09:48,255
Okay.

168
00:09:50,090 --> 00:09:52,467
I have to do what I can.

169
00:10:02,436 --> 00:10:03,854
Welcome.

170
00:10:14,740 --> 00:10:16,908
Hello. This is my first visit.

171
00:10:21,246 --> 00:10:23,165
The consultation fee is 3,000 yen.

172
00:10:23,999 --> 00:10:26,376
Please fill out this form.

173
00:10:30,088 --> 00:10:31,256
Yes.

174
00:10:47,022 --> 00:10:48,857
Oh, before I forget.

175
00:10:49,358 --> 00:10:51,234
Here. Take one.

176
00:10:51,777 --> 00:10:54,154
It's complimentary. One piece per guest.

177
00:10:58,075 --> 00:10:59,159
Sure.

178
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:14,966
Hey, Chloe.

179
00:11:15,634 --> 00:11:18,804
I think he's here. Molly.

180
00:11:19,679 --> 00:11:21,515
It's just a hunch, though.

181
00:11:21,598 --> 00:11:24,184
Sometimes your hunches are right.

182
00:11:24,267 --> 00:11:29,231
I prepared candy
as a gesture of our hospitality.

183
00:11:29,314 --> 00:11:31,108
What? That's lame.

184
00:11:31,191 --> 00:11:35,362
I got the candy you liked.
The popping, carbonated ones.

185
00:11:35,987 --> 00:11:37,239
KOMORI YUKIO

186
00:11:37,322 --> 00:11:40,659
Look at this name. It has to be fake.

187
00:11:41,451 --> 00:11:42,994
Komori Yukio.

188
00:11:44,663 --> 00:11:46,748
Is he a warlord, or what?

189
00:11:48,291 --> 00:11:52,212
If he read my reply and still came,

190
00:11:52,838 --> 00:11:54,339
then this may not be hopeless.

191
00:12:01,555 --> 00:12:02,556
APRIL 25TH, 1988

192
00:12:02,639 --> 00:12:05,976
Komori Yukio, 37 years old.

193
00:12:07,519 --> 00:12:09,521
Is this really the name
you're proceeding with?

194
00:12:10,147 --> 00:12:13,150
What's that supposed to mean?
That's my given name.

195
00:12:16,945 --> 00:12:18,238
Komori Yukio…

196
00:12:19,322 --> 00:12:20,866
Yukio Obayashi…

197
00:12:21,658 --> 00:12:22,742
Molly…

198
00:12:23,326 --> 00:12:24,453
Come again?

199
00:12:25,412 --> 00:12:29,166
I see. Komori Yukio, huh?

200
00:12:30,834 --> 00:12:33,712
I have no idea what you're getting at.

201
00:12:34,296 --> 00:12:37,215
Can you explain it to me
since this is my first session?

202
00:12:42,762 --> 00:12:45,974
On websites or in books,

203
00:12:46,057 --> 00:12:48,935
fortune telling is as simple
as entering your information.

204
00:12:49,728 --> 00:12:52,397
But that's not the case
with an in-person reading.

205
00:12:53,023 --> 00:12:56,776
Things I perceive from you
will directly alter the outcome.

206
00:12:57,652 --> 00:13:00,739
That's why the same cards can yield

207
00:13:00,822 --> 00:13:02,991
different interpretations
depending on the client.

208
00:13:03,783 --> 00:13:04,784
Really?

209
00:13:06,203 --> 00:13:10,290
But that's more like mind reading
and using mentalist techniques,

210
00:13:10,373 --> 00:13:12,459
not actually reading fortune, right?

211
00:13:12,542 --> 00:13:14,628
You're free to interpret it
however you wish.

212
00:13:16,213 --> 00:13:18,256
My job is to read your fortune.

213
00:13:18,340 --> 00:13:20,759
I don't use tricks,

214
00:13:20,842 --> 00:13:23,678
and I would never attempt
to induce a reaction from you.

215
00:13:24,679 --> 00:13:27,390
Also, the reading
may not always be accurate.

216
00:13:29,809 --> 00:13:33,021
So you're putting out a disclaimer

217
00:13:33,104 --> 00:13:35,440
that your predictions
don't always come true.

218
00:13:36,107 --> 00:13:37,859
What do you have to say about that?

219
00:13:39,528 --> 00:13:42,572
Fortune telling does not provide
an accurate prediction.

220
00:13:43,114 --> 00:13:45,909
Your action will determine your future.

221
00:13:49,829 --> 00:13:50,997
However…

222
00:13:53,250 --> 00:13:56,878
at times, fortune-telling
reaches beyond my reading.

223
00:13:56,962 --> 00:13:59,464
It can pinpoint the heart of the matter.

224
00:14:02,968 --> 00:14:05,220
Either way,

225
00:14:05,804 --> 00:14:08,223
it's up to you to find
the sincere question

226
00:14:08,723 --> 00:14:10,433
tucked somewhere in your heart.

227
00:14:12,936 --> 00:14:14,020
Well then,

228
00:14:14,771 --> 00:14:16,398
what brings you in today?

229
00:14:27,409 --> 00:14:28,577
My worries.

230
00:14:31,329 --> 00:14:32,455
Your worries…

231
00:14:33,540 --> 00:14:34,666
Is that correct?

232
00:14:37,502 --> 00:14:38,753
Understood.

233
00:14:39,337 --> 00:14:44,217
Let's see what the future holds
for your concern.

234
00:15:11,620 --> 00:15:12,662
Oh,

235
00:15:13,872 --> 00:15:14,998
mon…

236
00:15:15,707 --> 00:15:16,791
Dieu
!

237
00:15:27,761 --> 00:15:29,971
The first card.

238
00:15:30,889 --> 00:15:32,807
It represents your current situation.

239
00:15:35,602 --> 00:15:37,020
February, reversed.

240
00:15:37,103 --> 00:15:38,730
Card of Solitude.

241
00:15:39,939 --> 00:15:42,692
We are all lonely souls.

242
00:15:43,360 --> 00:15:44,694
But it's reversed.

243
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:47,697
Your loneliness
is taking you down a dark path.

244
00:15:49,157 --> 00:15:50,784
Your heart is in the right place,

245
00:15:51,368 --> 00:15:53,495
but because of your loneliness,
you've become twisted.

246
00:15:54,329 --> 00:15:56,456
Is that really what the card says?

247
00:15:57,499 --> 00:15:59,167
Or is that what you think of me?

248
00:16:02,504 --> 00:16:04,297
Yeah, I get it.

249
00:16:04,381 --> 00:16:05,924
You're pointing out what's wrong with me.

250
00:16:07,300 --> 00:16:08,635
Next card.

251
00:16:08,718 --> 00:16:11,930
It represents something from
the past that continues to affect you.

252
00:16:13,264 --> 00:16:16,142
November, reversed. Card of Fairness.

253
00:16:17,936 --> 00:16:19,104
There was something…

254
00:16:19,729 --> 00:16:22,857
that made you deeply feel
that life is unfair.

255
00:16:24,734 --> 00:16:26,611
I see a connection to the first card.

256
00:16:27,112 --> 00:16:30,448
You have a twisted sense of justice.

257
00:16:33,243 --> 00:16:34,494
No good…

258
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:37,747
ever comes to my life.

259
00:16:37,831 --> 00:16:39,207
C'est la vie.

260
00:16:40,917 --> 00:16:43,712
The third card. The inner self.

261
00:16:45,296 --> 00:16:47,924
July, upright. Card of Passion.

262
00:16:49,676 --> 00:16:52,762
There's a fire burning inside you.

263
00:16:53,346 --> 00:16:58,810
Silence. Meditation. Emotion. Freedom.

264
00:17:00,186 --> 00:17:01,604
Silence?

265
00:17:02,105 --> 00:17:03,690
You're telling me to shut up?

266
00:17:04,482 --> 00:17:07,485
Why not write instead of speaking out?

267
00:17:08,194 --> 00:17:12,323
However, your writing
should be carefully thought out.

268
00:17:13,324 --> 00:17:17,954
What? Come on,
I didn't leave a bad review.

269
00:17:19,622 --> 00:17:21,583
The fourth card. The outer world.

270
00:17:23,793 --> 00:17:26,755
Wednesday, upright. Card of Incident.

271
00:17:28,339 --> 00:17:30,800
Arrogance. Flaming.

272
00:17:30,884 --> 00:17:33,261
Hospital. Lightning strike.

273
00:17:35,597 --> 00:17:40,059
It could be either physical or emotional.

274
00:17:40,143 --> 00:17:41,269
You may get involved in an incident.

275
00:17:43,438 --> 00:17:44,939
You're kidding.

276
00:17:45,857 --> 00:17:47,317
It's upright,

277
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:50,653
meaning this incident
will benefit you in the end.

278
00:17:51,446 --> 00:17:55,867
But you may want to brace yourself
so it doesn't catch you by surprise.

279
00:17:55,950 --> 00:17:57,243
What?

280
00:17:58,828 --> 00:18:00,663
Like what, I'll get backlash online?

281
00:18:01,623 --> 00:18:05,752
Are you gonna start a fight online
because you're upset about the review?

282
00:18:07,420 --> 00:18:10,965
You've basically admitted you're Molly,

283
00:18:11,049 --> 00:18:12,133
Yukio Komori.

284
00:18:12,217 --> 00:18:15,553
The cat's out of the bag.
You even dug up my real name.

285
00:18:17,055 --> 00:18:21,559
I will take appropriate measures
against someone who causes me harm.

286
00:18:22,602 --> 00:18:25,688
However, when clients
come to me sincerely seeking guidance,

287
00:18:25,772 --> 00:18:31,361
I face them hoping to steer them
in the right direction.

288
00:18:31,444 --> 00:18:34,155
That's why you're here, right?

289
00:18:38,076 --> 00:18:39,869
That's why, although reversed,

290
00:18:39,953 --> 00:18:41,746
you gave me your real name.

291
00:18:42,455 --> 00:18:43,915
Right, Komori Yukio?

292
00:18:48,837 --> 00:18:50,171
The final card.

293
00:18:51,047 --> 00:18:53,716
It represents an event in the near future.

294
00:18:56,219 --> 00:18:59,389
June, upright. Card of Crossroads.

295
00:19:03,226 --> 00:19:06,312
The cards representing
your past and present were reversed,

296
00:19:06,396 --> 00:19:09,482
but those representing
your inner self, outer world,

297
00:19:09,566 --> 00:19:11,359
and near future are upright.

298
00:19:12,527 --> 00:19:15,989
You'll soon stand at a crossroads.
One that will better your life.

299
00:19:17,323 --> 00:19:18,491
However…

300
00:19:19,284 --> 00:19:20,285
However?

301
00:19:20,368 --> 00:19:22,620
…as I said at the start,

302
00:19:22,704 --> 00:19:24,789
your actions determine your future.

303
00:19:25,665 --> 00:19:29,043
Be careful that you do not direct
your sincerity,

304
00:19:29,711 --> 00:19:34,215
sense of justice, and passion
to the wrong cause.

305
00:19:36,634 --> 00:19:38,177
Even if you face backlash online,

306
00:19:38,845 --> 00:19:42,891
you'll find a way
to make something good out of it.

307
00:19:44,100 --> 00:19:45,101
Um…

308
00:19:45,727 --> 00:19:47,770
Is the backlash part definite?

309
00:19:49,772 --> 00:19:54,027
Card of Crossroads
may refer to electronic devices.

310
00:19:54,110 --> 00:19:55,612
So I'd say yes.

311
00:19:56,738 --> 00:19:58,031
No way.

312
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:02,493
Now, your lucky color is light green.

313
00:20:03,828 --> 00:20:06,539
I don't own anything in light green.

314
00:20:09,876 --> 00:20:13,838
INSECT SPRAY

315
00:20:30,605 --> 00:20:32,482
Don't worry, I won't bite.

316
00:20:33,441 --> 00:20:34,817
I hope you had a good reading.

317
00:20:34,901 --> 00:20:36,527
I won't write negative reviews anymore.

318
00:20:37,654 --> 00:20:38,696
Okay.

319
00:20:45,161 --> 00:20:47,121
Did you take one?

320
00:20:47,789 --> 00:20:50,041
I'm good. Not a fan of candy.

321
00:20:56,798 --> 00:20:58,091
Light green.

322
00:20:59,717 --> 00:21:01,219
Cream soda candy.

323
00:21:01,302 --> 00:21:03,721
It's pretty good.
I've been obsessed with it.

324
00:21:04,973 --> 00:21:06,265
Then, I'll take it.

325
00:21:09,894 --> 00:21:12,355
Thank you.

326
00:21:22,865 --> 00:21:24,534
Phew, I'm wiped.

327
00:21:24,617 --> 00:21:25,868
Great work in there.

328
00:21:25,952 --> 00:21:28,079
Can I have a piece of your cheap candy?

329
00:21:29,247 --> 00:21:30,331
Here you go.

330
00:21:31,040 --> 00:21:33,209
Nice going. You vanquished Molly.

331
00:21:34,002 --> 00:21:36,254
I wouldn't say vanquished…

332
00:21:37,005 --> 00:21:39,007
Here's how I'd describe him.

333
00:21:39,090 --> 00:21:42,802
He can't resist pitching in his two cents.

334
00:21:42,885 --> 00:21:44,804
His heart's in the right place,

335
00:21:44,887 --> 00:21:48,307
but he's ashamed to show it.
It's like he can't help it.

336
00:21:52,645 --> 00:21:55,356
Like, by hating on my candy,
calling it cheap and stuff?

337
00:21:57,942 --> 00:22:00,194
This wholesale candy
comes individually packed.

338
00:22:00,278 --> 00:22:02,280
All candy from wholesale bags are cheap.

339
00:22:03,740 --> 00:22:04,991
Sorry, I'm back.

340
00:22:06,325 --> 00:22:08,828
Where'd you get this candy, Miss?

341
00:22:10,913 --> 00:22:14,917
I thought it was just regular
popping candy, but it's good.

342
00:22:15,001 --> 00:22:17,754
Right? Isn't it delicious?

343
00:22:17,837 --> 00:22:20,715
I looked up the brand.
Apparently, it's discontinued.

344
00:22:20,798 --> 00:22:22,175
Really?

345
00:22:22,258 --> 00:22:25,803
I found it in the clearance section
of the pharmacy by the station.

346
00:22:25,887 --> 00:22:28,014
Thank you. I'll go check it out.

347
00:22:28,806 --> 00:22:30,141
-Thank you.
-My pleasure.

348
00:22:40,109 --> 00:22:44,072
Molly might be more sincere than you are.

349
00:22:54,040 --> 00:22:56,167
TRADITIONAL CAFÉ PARIS

350
00:22:56,250 --> 00:22:58,211
It's been on my mind
since Emma pointed it out.

351
00:22:58,920 --> 00:23:02,507
I… choose who I hate on.

352
00:23:13,559 --> 00:23:17,980
Like, I'd never have an attitude with you.

353
00:23:18,898 --> 00:23:20,274
Of course,

354
00:23:20,358 --> 00:23:24,153
there's the power dynamic between
an employer and an employee.

355
00:23:25,988 --> 00:23:27,156
But more importantly,

356
00:23:28,032 --> 00:23:32,745
I want to be seen as a good older sister.
I don't want you to hate me.

357
00:23:38,167 --> 00:23:40,962
You're like a wonderful
older sister to me, Chloe.

358
00:23:49,137 --> 00:23:50,429
Also, like…

359
00:23:51,514 --> 00:23:55,351
what if I'm too nice to Emma,
and she overstays her welcome?

360
00:23:57,019 --> 00:23:58,062
That's why

361
00:23:59,105 --> 00:24:00,898
I deliberately draw a line.

362
00:24:01,732 --> 00:24:05,278
I think that's what it is.

363
00:24:16,497 --> 00:24:19,625
TWO WEEKS LATER

364
00:24:19,709 --> 00:24:20,710
You're saying…

365
00:24:21,669 --> 00:24:24,130
Molly went viral because of this candy?

366
00:24:24,213 --> 00:24:25,298
Yes.

367
00:24:25,381 --> 00:24:27,175
That's exactly it.

368
00:24:27,258 --> 00:24:30,136
This cheap candy is trending
on social media.

369
00:24:30,219 --> 00:24:33,472
The viral post is by an account
named Snow Tail.

370
00:24:33,556 --> 00:24:36,767
Molly's alias was Komori Yukio.

371
00:24:36,851 --> 00:24:39,812
"Yuki" meaning "Snow"
and "O" meaning "Tail."

372
00:24:39,896 --> 00:24:40,980
In other words, "Snow Tail."

373
00:24:41,063 --> 00:24:43,441
SNOW TAIL - THOUGHT THIS CANDY
WOULD "SUCK," BUT IT'S GOOD

374
00:24:43,524 --> 00:24:45,234
He spammed his account

375
00:24:45,318 --> 00:24:49,488
with the love for the cheap candy
and store links to buy them.

376
00:24:49,572 --> 00:24:51,949
Apparently, this candy was widely loved.

377
00:24:52,033 --> 00:24:53,701
His post got over 10,000 likes.

378
00:24:54,827 --> 00:24:56,162
That's amazing.

379
00:24:56,245 --> 00:24:59,457
I thought the reading said
he would face backlash.

380
00:24:59,540 --> 00:25:00,750
That's the thing.

381
00:25:00,833 --> 00:25:03,753
I looked at the reposts.
He got some hate comments.

382
00:25:05,713 --> 00:25:07,048
What is it?

383
00:25:07,131 --> 00:25:08,841
Molly deleted his account.

384
00:25:09,508 --> 00:25:11,302
I wonder if something happened to him.

385
00:25:11,886 --> 00:25:13,930
Sounds like someone got attached.

386
00:25:14,013 --> 00:25:15,348
But that's not all.

387
00:25:16,349 --> 00:25:20,853
I already tracked down his personal blog.

388
00:25:20,937 --> 00:25:22,521
This again?

389
00:25:22,605 --> 00:25:24,565
Seems like I'm not
the only one who got attached.

390
00:25:25,399 --> 00:25:27,485
Or are you just curious?

391
00:25:28,903 --> 00:25:32,156
His latest post is about the backlash.

392
00:25:32,240 --> 00:25:33,491
Let me see.

393
00:25:36,869 --> 00:25:41,457
"The backlash I faced
over the cream soda candy

394
00:25:41,540 --> 00:25:43,834
led me to delete my account."

395
00:25:48,839 --> 00:25:53,302
I wanted to write down my take
on this situation

396
00:25:53,386 --> 00:25:55,721
in my blog.

397
00:25:58,307 --> 00:26:02,395
"It all started when a business I visited
gave me complimentary candy.

398
00:26:02,478 --> 00:26:05,856
The cream soda-flavored candy
was out of this world."

399
00:26:06,524 --> 00:26:08,317
I'm such a sucker.

400
00:26:08,901 --> 00:26:10,152
You know, as in candy.

401
00:26:12,113 --> 00:26:14,073
I thought it'd be a simple
soda-flavored candy,

402
00:26:14,156 --> 00:26:16,325
but the hardened part itself
is milk-flavored.

403
00:26:16,409 --> 00:26:17,576
The core

404
00:26:17,660 --> 00:26:21,664
is a melon gummy
with a powerful popping coating.

405
00:26:21,747 --> 00:26:24,375
I instantly became a fan of this gimmick.

406
00:26:24,875 --> 00:26:28,879
I thought it was just regular
popping candy, but it's good.

407
00:26:30,631 --> 00:26:33,551
Unfortunately, it's been discontinued.

408
00:26:33,634 --> 00:26:36,178
Most stores don't carry it.

409
00:26:36,887 --> 00:26:38,389
I put so much effort into finding it.

410
00:26:40,016 --> 00:26:41,976
CREAM SODA CANDY

411
00:26:46,939 --> 00:26:51,027
I made a post raving about it,
and somehow, it went viral.

412
00:26:51,110 --> 00:26:53,070
I was so surprised.

413
00:26:53,154 --> 00:26:54,238
YOU CAN STILL BUY IT?

414
00:26:54,322 --> 00:26:56,032
My notifications were popping.

415
00:26:57,116 --> 00:26:58,451
Like soda pop.

416
00:27:00,703 --> 00:27:03,080
He sure loves puns.

417
00:27:03,831 --> 00:27:07,335
His witty puns must be why it went viral.

418
00:27:09,545 --> 00:27:13,299
"But just as flies are attracted
to delicious food,

419
00:27:13,382 --> 00:27:15,885
the buzz I stirred
got the attentions of gnats."

420
00:27:16,427 --> 00:27:17,595
"Buzz…"

421
00:27:18,346 --> 00:27:19,347
"Gnats."

422
00:27:22,391 --> 00:27:23,434
There!

423
00:27:23,517 --> 00:27:25,436
I grew up in the digital age.

424
00:27:25,519 --> 00:27:27,271
SUCK AS IN CANDY? SO LAME
NOW YOU ACT NICE?

425
00:27:27,355 --> 00:27:29,440
I know how to deal with haters.

426
00:27:29,523 --> 00:27:30,858
SOUNDS LIKE HE HAS NO LIFE

427
00:27:30,941 --> 00:27:34,862
I can deal with them, but the hate
comments started to open my eyes.

428
00:27:34,945 --> 00:27:36,655
IS IT EVEN THAT GOOD?
I BET IT'S A PAID AD

429
00:27:37,782 --> 00:27:42,286
I realized I'm a hater, just like them.

430
00:27:45,664 --> 00:27:46,957
Molly…

431
00:27:50,294 --> 00:27:54,882
"I'll come clean.
Recently, I left a hate comment,

432
00:27:54,965 --> 00:27:58,386
and someone gave me such a scathing reply
that I ended up deleting my post."

433
00:27:58,469 --> 00:27:59,470
SWEET-TOOTHED GEEZER

434
00:28:00,846 --> 00:28:04,683
Like, I'm well in my 30s, but I don't
have a stable job, and I'm single.

435
00:28:05,351 --> 00:28:08,979
But I have to provide for my family.
I'm the head of the household.

436
00:28:10,398 --> 00:28:12,858
It's like I'm constantly dealt
the losing hand in the game of life.

437
00:28:14,402 --> 00:28:15,945
To cover up my insecurity,

438
00:28:16,028 --> 00:28:19,615
I respond to everything
by mocking it first.

439
00:28:20,574 --> 00:28:23,160
I try to make people laugh
by tearing others down.

440
00:28:24,286 --> 00:28:27,415
For the sake of my own pride,

441
00:28:27,498 --> 00:28:31,585
I began ridiculing others,
and it's become who I am.

442
00:28:31,669 --> 00:28:33,504
Oh, no. We should say sorry.

443
00:28:33,587 --> 00:28:37,299
-
But when I finally found something…
-Sorry, Mister, can you toss the ball?

444
00:28:37,383 --> 00:28:38,884
-
…that gave me a spark of joy…
-Here.

445
00:28:38,968 --> 00:28:43,222
I got hated on
by the kind of person I used to be.

446
00:28:45,266 --> 00:28:47,351
Karma's a bitch. Ha.

447
00:28:48,602 --> 00:28:51,897
These haters are just like me.

448
00:28:56,152 --> 00:28:59,405
"In the end, I was the one
who got sucker-punched by life.

449
00:29:00,072 --> 00:29:01,323
Get it? Like a sucker."

450
00:29:03,993 --> 00:29:07,204
He kept up his puns to the very end.

451
00:29:11,542 --> 00:29:13,169
Wait, he wrote some more.

452
00:29:17,590 --> 00:29:21,135
Rock, paper, scissors, shoot,
we split into teams.

453
00:29:21,218 --> 00:29:22,803
Shoot.

454
00:29:22,887 --> 00:29:24,388
Shoot.

455
00:29:25,431 --> 00:29:29,018
Still, it was fun
to get my 15 seconds of fame.

456
00:29:29,560 --> 00:29:34,231
Even celebrities shared my post,
and my number of followers skyrocketed.

457
00:29:34,315 --> 00:29:35,316
Yuma!

458
00:29:35,399 --> 00:29:38,068
So it wasn't all that bad.

459
00:29:39,403 --> 00:29:44,575
Still, fear won out in the end.

460
00:29:47,786 --> 00:29:51,582
I had more fun looking for the stores,

461
00:29:51,665 --> 00:29:53,959
and it made me happy
when I found the candy in stock.

462
00:29:54,668 --> 00:29:55,961
There.

463
00:29:56,629 --> 00:29:59,548
It was fun to write
about something I'm passionate about,

464
00:30:00,466 --> 00:30:03,219
and it made me happy
that people liked my writing.

465
00:30:03,802 --> 00:30:04,887
Would you like one?

466
00:30:07,973 --> 00:30:09,266
-I have the same one.
-It's good!

467
00:30:09,350 --> 00:30:13,437
He has the same one.
Let's eat it together.

468
00:30:13,521 --> 00:30:15,731
It's yummy.

469
00:30:15,814 --> 00:30:17,608
I could eat a hundred of 'em!

470
00:30:17,691 --> 00:30:18,943
-Not a hundred.
-
How do I put it?

471
00:30:19,443 --> 00:30:25,115
It's okay for happiness to be this cheap.

472
00:30:25,199 --> 00:30:26,700
That was good.

473
00:30:27,535 --> 00:30:30,371
Oh, Molly. Now I've got the feels.

474
00:30:32,456 --> 00:30:35,125
He chose the right path.

475
00:30:37,378 --> 00:30:39,129
Thank you for waiting.

476
00:30:44,385 --> 00:30:47,263
This week, I made pop rock candy parfait.

477
00:30:50,849 --> 00:30:52,560
-Thank you.
-Here you go.

478
00:30:54,770 --> 00:30:58,524
The bottom layer is vanilla mousse
with lemon and mint jelly.

479
00:30:59,233 --> 00:31:01,360
There's melon and pistachio cookies,

480
00:31:02,444 --> 00:31:04,196
and avocado and banana mousse.

481
00:31:04,280 --> 00:31:07,199
On the top is melon and carbonated jelly,

482
00:31:07,283 --> 00:31:09,785
vanilla ice cream with popping candy,

483
00:31:09,868 --> 00:31:11,954
and a whipped blend
of heavy and sour cream.

484
00:31:12,037 --> 00:31:14,498
And of course, I added the cherry on top.

485
00:31:14,582 --> 00:31:15,833
Bon appétit.

486
00:31:15,916 --> 00:31:17,167
What a presentation.

487
00:31:17,251 --> 00:31:19,461
-Everything is green.
-Yes.

488
00:31:19,545 --> 00:31:21,589
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

489
00:31:33,475 --> 00:31:35,144
Ooh, it's popping.

490
00:31:35,769 --> 00:31:37,730
Only the top part pops.

491
00:31:37,813 --> 00:31:40,316
Everything below the melon
is normal parfait.

492
00:31:40,399 --> 00:31:44,737
Please enjoy the fruits' natural sweetness
with the mousse and jelly.

493
00:31:45,863 --> 00:31:49,783
Thrill is fun, but only in small doses.

494
00:31:50,743 --> 00:31:52,077
I know, right?

495
00:31:52,161 --> 00:31:55,831
Stability and safety
are what's important in life.

496
00:31:57,041 --> 00:32:00,377
I like to see my creativity take shape.

497
00:32:00,461 --> 00:32:02,171
That's what I enjoy the most.

498
00:32:04,673 --> 00:32:08,260
What about you?
What do you find important in life?

499
00:32:12,473 --> 00:32:13,641
Nothing.

500
00:32:15,184 --> 00:32:17,227
But you have everything already.

501
00:32:18,646 --> 00:32:20,356
Maybe having everything

502
00:32:21,148 --> 00:32:22,316
is just another way to say…

503
00:32:22,941 --> 00:32:25,402
that nothing actually belongs to you.

504
00:32:26,904 --> 00:32:29,239
Just like the "taste of home."

505
00:32:58,686 --> 00:33:00,437
How many eggs per person?

506
00:33:00,938 --> 00:33:02,398
Just one.

507
00:33:02,481 --> 00:33:03,565
Really?

508
00:33:04,066 --> 00:33:05,943
Wouldn't it taste better if I used more?

509
00:33:07,736 --> 00:33:09,279
I'm gonna use three.

510
00:33:11,156 --> 00:33:12,616
How luxurious.

511
00:33:20,666 --> 00:33:24,920
Mine never quite tastes like my mom's.

512
00:33:25,003 --> 00:33:27,256
I thought she taught it to you.

513
00:33:27,339 --> 00:33:30,426
Well, we never actually made it together.

514
00:33:30,509 --> 00:33:33,053
Mine never turns out as fluffy as hers.

515
00:33:34,179 --> 00:33:35,389
Fluffy?

516
00:33:44,857 --> 00:33:46,233
Mayonnaise?

517
00:33:47,526 --> 00:33:50,529
It makes the eggs fluffier.

518
00:33:51,363 --> 00:33:52,948
Really?

519
00:33:59,747 --> 00:34:00,831
Here.

520
00:34:04,626 --> 00:34:05,753
There.

521
00:34:34,406 --> 00:34:36,116
Looks delicious.

522
00:34:37,618 --> 00:34:39,453
-Thank you.
-Time to dig in.

523
00:34:55,719 --> 00:34:58,889
This is closer to my mom's
than what I make.

524
00:34:58,972 --> 00:35:00,182
Really?

525
00:35:02,267 --> 00:35:05,270
My mom must've used mayonnaise.

526
00:35:16,031 --> 00:35:18,116
Thank you, Chloe.

527
00:35:19,743 --> 00:35:23,205
The Emma family's taste of home
belongs to you now.

528
00:35:23,288 --> 00:35:24,289
Why me?

529
00:35:24,373 --> 00:35:27,042
It doesn't matter to whom
a family recipe gets handed down.

530
00:35:27,125 --> 00:35:29,753
The real recipe was lost
until today anyway.

531
00:35:35,926 --> 00:35:36,927
Sure.

532
00:35:41,139 --> 00:35:42,140
Okay.

533
00:35:42,683 --> 00:35:45,435
Guess I'll inherit the Emma family's
taste of home.

534
00:35:45,519 --> 00:35:46,937
Yes!

535
00:35:48,230 --> 00:35:50,023
Though, it's cheap.

536
00:35:50,524 --> 00:35:52,943
That's what makes it
the Emma family's flavor.

537
00:36:39,990 --> 00:36:41,491
Digging in.

538
00:39:16,146 --> 00:39:17,898
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

539
00:39:17,981 --> 00:39:19,983
Subtitle: Megumi Hunter
